      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Para resolver el problema (6.24) mediante el método de los multiplicadores de Lagrange, definimos la restricción\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.eq-scroll}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "g\\left( x,y \\right) =x^{2}+y^{2}-1\n",
        "\\tag{6.25}\n",
        "$$\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "Luego, construimos el Lagrangiano asociado, obteniendo\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.eq-scroll}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\begin{array}{lll}\\mathcal{L} \\left( x,y,\\lambda \\right)&=&f\\left( x,y \\right) +\\lambda g\\left( x,y \\right)\\\\ &=&x+y+\\lambda \\left( x^{2}+y^{2}-1 \\right)\\end{array}\n",
        "\\tag{6.26}\n",
        "$$\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "De esta manera, las condiciones de primer orden del problema vienen dadas por\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.eq-scroll}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\begin{array}{l}\\dfrac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial x} =1+2\\lambda x=0\\\\ \\dfrac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial y} =1+2\\lambda y=0\\\\ \\dfrac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial \\lambda} =x^{2}+y^{2}-1=0\\end{array}\n",
        "\\tag{6.27}\n",
        "$$\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "Como antes, a fin de ayudarnos con Python a resolver este problema de forma simbólica, haremos uso de la librería **<font color='darkmagenta'>Sympy</font>**:"
      ],
      "id": "0fa0381a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Definimos las variables simbólicas del problema.\n",
        "x, y = sym.symbols(\"x, y\", real=True)\n",
        "lam = sym.symbols(r\"\\lambda\", real=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Construimos el Lagrangiano.\n",
        "L = x + y + lam*(x**2 + y**2 - 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mostramos el Lagrangiano en pantalla.\n",
        "L"
      ],
      "id": "3611ed84",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Calculamos ahora las derivadas parciales de $\\mathcal{L}$ con respecto a las variables reales y al multiplicador de Lagrange:"
      ],
      "id": "d81a1550"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Derivadas parciales del Lagrangiano.\n",
        "dL_dx = L.diff(x)\n",
        "dL_dy = L.diff(y)\n",
        "dL_dlam = L.diff(lam)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mostramos las derivadas en pantalla.\n",
        "dL_dx, dL_dy, dL_dlam"
      ],
      "id": "78a9912a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Igualando estas expresiones a cero, obtenemos el sistema no lineal que caracteriza a los puntos críticos del problema:"
      ],
      "id": "e9107677"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Resolvemos el sistema de ecuaciones de Lagrange.\n",
        "result = sym.solve(\n",
        "    [dL_dx, dL_dy, dL_dlam],\n",
        "    [x, y, lam],\n",
        "    dict=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mostramos el resultado.\n",
        "result"
      ],
      "id": "1209244b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Para determinar la naturaleza de estos puntos, evaluamos la función objetivo en cada uno de ellos:"
      ],
      "id": "b031c924"
